    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "- BRANIFF INTERNATIONAL\n000000000000000000000@ecccooooc\n011111111",
      "Flying Colors\nof the United States\nCalder\nPainted by Alexander Calder to represent\nthe red, white and blue of the Nation's flag\nin motion as a tribute to the 200th birthday\nof the United States. The identification of the\nairline does not appear on the jet, only the\nsignature of Calder. Since its dedication in\nWashington on November 17, 1975, the\nflagship of the Braniff International jet fleet has\nbeen in scheduled service to the 40 cities\nserved by the airline, flying some 1,200,000\nmiles a year. Since there can be only one\n\"Flying Colors of the United States,\" all other\naircraft in Braniff's fleet carry the name,\n\"Flying Colors.\"\nBraniff gets you there with Flying Colors.\n2015 16b. 2511"
    ],
